parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the clutch pedal to become unstable, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal pops and becomes unstable

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden disengagement of the cruise control can cause the vehicle to slow down unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The cruise control shuts off suddenly
the cruise control will not re-engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of the ABS can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose traction, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ABS engages when starting to drive in first and second gear
the vehicle slows down or loses traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump and Lockring Gasket Assembly Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leakage can cause a fire hazard, leading to vehicle damage or personal injury. It can also lead to costly repairs and potential environmental damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Loss of Throttle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and loss of throttle control can cause the vehicle to accelerate rapidly, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without input from the driver
the cruise control does not disengage
the vehicle does not respond to braking or clutch input
the engine continues to rev even after the vehicle is stopped.

which gradually increase in size over time
